parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to become inoperable, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle does not remain in the latch mechanism
the seat belt buckle does not latch
the seat belt release button is defective
the seat belt buckle fastens and then pops out with any movement
the seat belt will not stay fastened.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor does not retract backward
the seat belt retractor/belt clip fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden detachment of the headliner while driving can cause a distraction to the driver, potentially leading to accidents or injuries. Additionally, the exposure of fiberglass material underneath the headliner can cause skin irritation or other health issues.
symptoms: The headliner falls or detaches from the roof of the vehicle while driving
and potentially causing skin contact or irritation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Engine Control Module (ECM) can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies while driving
the check engine light is illuminated
the vehicle experiences poor engine performance
the vehicle experiences reduced power or hesitation.
